# {{title}}

Scaffolded by `create-biotope-scenario`. The manifest, narrative, and asset
folders are ready to author against. Run the validator after edits:

```bash
npm run scenario:validate -- .
```

## Layout

```
{{slug}}/
  manifest.yaml         # bd-rntm.1 schema; this is the contract
  narrative/
    en.ink              # English narrative; every node referenced from
                        # manifest must exist here
  scenes/
    main.glb            # 3D scene (placeholder; replace with your asset)
  species/              # scenario-local species pack data
  species.json
  region/               # references to a shared region pack
```

## Authoring loop

1. Edit `manifest.yaml` and `narrative/en.ink` together. Every
   `narrative_node` you add to the manifest needs a matching knot/stitch
   in the .ink file.
2. Replace `scenes/main.glb` with your real Draco-compressed +
   KTX2-textured glTF.
3. `npm run scenario:validate -- .`
4. Iterate.

See `docs/biotope-mvp-planning.md` §2 for the full manifest spec.
